******
[2] Kyrgyzstan (Karasuv)
Date: Fri 24 Jun 2005
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: AkiPress news agency [translated by Mod.NR, edited]
<http://fergana.akipress.org/?id=16521>


New cases of typhoid reported in Karasuv
-------------------------------------------
14 cases of typhoid fever have been reported in the Karasuv rayon. 11
cases out of the 14 came from Karasuv. Since 27 May 2005, an urgent
epidemiologic situation has been declared in Kyrgyzstan.

According to epidemiologic disease surveillance official Akilbek
Isayevhim, the sanitary epidemiological surveillance station has
conducted assessments in 94 epidemiologically dangerous places. 5 of
these places have been closed, and 6 institutional chiefs have been
fined. 17 water pipes were sterilized using chlorine in Karasuv.
Despite all of these measures, 2 more cases of typhoid fever have
been reported in Karasuv.

--
